áin’s seven main concerns: poetry and its place in the artist’s life; the plural self; the relationship between the individual and society; gender relations; the nature of animals; Ireland, its language and culture; and mortality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aIrish poetryvTranslations into English. 7aPOETRY / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh1 aSewell, Frank, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z97831106725030 cprintz978030019058840uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030020836840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300208368423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300208368/original  a978-3-11-067250-3  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY